[[meta title="Duplex printing - use mpage"]]
My favourite option:
 mpage -t -2 -Pprintername your.ps
 hendry@bogrund-14:~$ mpage -t -Pps8 agiledev.ps
 hendry@bogrund-14:~$ lpq -Pps8
 net-ps8 is ready and printing
 Rank   Owner      Job  Files                                 Total Size
 active hendry     80   (standard input)                      1097686 bytes
 hendry@bogrund-14:~$ mpage --help
 mpage: unknown option --
 mpage - print multiple pages on postscript, version 2.5.1pre2 March 1998
 mpage [-1248acEfHlkoOrRStvxX] [-b papersize] [-Btextboxmargin]
       [-C [encodingfile]] [-da|p] [-D dateformat] [-F fontname]
       [-h header] [-I indent] [-j pagespec] [-L lines]
       [-msheetmargin] [-Mpagemargin] [-p[prprog]] [-P[printer]]
       [-s tabstop] [-W width] [-X [header]] [-z printcmd] [-Z quearg]
       [file...]]
 -1, -2, -4, -8  Pages per sheet (4)    -D strftime format for date specs
 -da Force ascii input format           -dp Force postscript input format
 -a Toggle across/updown layout (u)     -l Toggle portrait/landscape (p)
 -f Toggle folding long lines (off)     -o Toggle printing outlines (on)
 -r Reverse printing, last->first sheet -v Toggle verbose output, (on)
 -F Text font to be used (Courier)      -C Character encoding filename
 -E Print every second and third page   -O Print every first and fourth page
 -s Define tabstop width (8)            -k kill on %TRailer is PS file
 -b papersize (Letter), use l of ? to get a list of sizes
 -R Switch to across mode, with first page at lower left corner
 -H Create page header for each page for text files
 -X Print physical page header (filename + physical pagenumber)
 -c Toggle concat pages of different files on same sheet (off)
 -S Don't square pages for PS input (default uniform X/Y shrink)
 -B Specify textbox margin/thickness (no space): [<num>[lrtb]*]*
 -m Specify sheetmargin (no space): [<num>[lrtb]*]*
 -M Specify pagemargins (no space): [<num>[lrtb]*]*
 -p Pipe through prprog (no space), pr(1) is default.
    Mpage assumes the specified pr understands -l, -w and -h options.
 -P Specify printer queue (no space). -P only uses default queue.
 -z Specify print command (lpr).
 -Z Specify print command print queue option (-P).
 -j Print specified sheets: first[-last][%interval]
    -j 1-10 does first 10 sheets, -j 1%2 prints odd ones, -j 2%2 even ones.
 -t Toggle printing both sides of the paper (Duplex mode, off)
 -T Toggle tumble of every second pages when printing in duplex mode (off)
